---
title: Fall Detection — 3-Phase State Machine with SOS
---
stateDiagram-v2

    [*] --> Idle

    Idle --> Freefall : SV < 0.5g
    Freefall --> Impact : SV > 2.5g (within 300ms)
    Freefall --> Idle : timeout (no impact)
    Impact --> Inactivity : SV ~ 1g
    Impact --> Idle : another impact
    Inactivity --> Confirmed : still 1g for 2s
    Inactivity --> Idle : SV > 2.5g or < 0.5g
    Confirmed --> CancelWindow : beep 800Hz
    CancelWindow --> SOSAlarm : 10s timeout
    CancelWindow --> Idle : button press (cancel)
    SOSAlarm --> Idle : 3 SOS cycles done

    note left of Idle
        AI active = reset to Idle
        (user pressing button = not falling)
    end note
    note right of Freefall
        Phase 1: SV < 0.5g (4.9 m/s^2)
        Free-fall detected
    end note
    note right of Impact
        Phase 2: SV > 2.5g (24.5 m/s^2)
        Within 300ms after free-fall
    end note
    note right of Inactivity
        Phase 3: SV ~ 1g (9.8 m/s^2)
        Sustained for 2000ms
    end note
    note right of CancelWindow
        SOS = 3 short + 3 long + 3 short
        I2S speaker at max volume
        10s window to cancel
    end note
